e only Japanese woman filmmaker between 1953 and 1962, and her films tackled distinctly feminine topics such as prostitution and breast cancer. Her career overlapped with a transformative period in Japanese history, and this close analysis of her fascinating life and work offers new perspectives, subjectivities and modes of analysis for the classical era of Japanese cinema.Key FeaturesA unique look at the life and career of Tanaka Kinuyo, as both an actor and directorOffers a new perspective on the history of women and film in JapanBrings together a range of Japanese and western scholars  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aElectronic books. 0aMotion picture actors and actresseszJapany20th centuryvBiography. 0aMotion picture producers and directorszJapany20th centuryvBiography. 0aWomen motion picture producers and directorszJapany20th centuryvBiography. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh1 aArmendáriz-Hernández, Alejandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález-López, Irene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacoby, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanno, Yuka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaoru, Furukawa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKitsnik, Lauri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMayu, Ashida, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaito, Ayako, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSmith, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is p